{
  "texts": [
    "Activating congruent schemas impacts how people judge the agent and its actions.",
    "For example, the belief that you share the same phenomenological experience with a robot changes the way you view its level of intent or agency (Marchesi et al., 2022).",
    "Activation of mindsimilarity may resemble simulation theory (Harris, 1992; Röska-Hardy, 2008).",
    "In that hypothesis, the observer does not merely believe the artificial agent has a mind but simulates that mind through the neural machinery of the person's own mind.",
    "Simulation allows the agent to seem more familiar, which facilitates interaction."
  ]
}